rComments: Dr. Dion is probably the best prof chem prof at uOttawar! She's an amazing teacher! Midterms are easy. Obviously you have to put in the work. The final is the easiest! Nothing about theory, just practice & practice & practice the mechanisms and you can easily pass the class with an A.
Tres bon professeur qui aime enseigner!

Worst prof of my life. Everything she doesn't specify in her notes, she gives at the exam. There's a trick in every question, EVERY. Exams do not show if you understand organic chem, always to long. Lot of A's in her class,all on Adderall, I guess I missed the message we are supposed to use drugs to be able to do everything! I would change teachers

She's a good prof, explains well, notes are clear (although sometimes she goes fast and writes gibberish). Do the assignments, thoroughly look at the old exams (the have same structure) and you'll do fine. Look at similarities in the mechanisms, theres about 30 in the course. To get A- or higher, you need to work really hard.
Such a good prof! Go to her classes and do the assignments and you will do well in her class! Also, I found the CHM2120 DGD's REALLY helpful, so I recommend treating them like classes and go to them!

Great Prof. Her lectures are fairly organized and very straight forward. I liked how she did a review of the things previously learned at the start of each class. She does her best to make herself available to the students and is always willing to help. Recommend her 100%. also, i didn't use the textbook once for this class, its seriously a waste!

Best prof ever. Crystal clear explanations and examples in class.  Go visit her office hours for help or life talk. She is so popular that her office is always full of visitors. Extremely knowledgeable about synthesis and mechanisms, she is a big fan of synthesis questions.

Meilleur professeur que j'avais rencontré à l'univesité d'Ottawa.Les examens sont trop justes et reflètent très bien le contenu du cours et les devoirs. Très serviable et prette à répondre aux questions poses dans la classe et Durant les heures de bureau. Recommandé fortement !!
BEST PROF EVER, super helpful and her midterms and finals reflect her assignments completely, definitely recommend!

I thought Dr. Louiseau was an amazing prof Orgo I prof until I got into Orgo II with Dr. Dion. Her notes are crystal clear, her assignments reflect her exams. Super sweet and helpful when you ask plus she's funny in class. BEST PROF EVER! Thanks Dr. Dion! :)

Isabelle Dion was the best professor I've ever had at the University of Ottawa. She was very clear about what was expected. Exams were fair, you knew what ideas would be tested. I would recommend her to anyone!

The best prof I have had at uOttawa yet. Very helpful answering questions during the class and during office hours (she will even help you with CHM 2123 lab questions as well). The "Last Lecture" reviews she does at the beginning of each class are extremely helpful. Exams were very fair, although don't just memorize, know your theory.

Best Orgo prof! Good lecturer, clear notes, fair exams, responds to emails,  very approachable and offers lots of office hrs. Makes lectures as least boring as possible. She is a straight up genuine nice professor. The only thing that I don't like is her policy of regrading tests in class.

She makes organic chem make sense, and is super nice doing so. She always has unintentional jokes that keep the class funny. Office hours are so useful, she even helped with the lab course. I actually kinda like organic chem now. Highly recommended.

AMAZING PROF! Her notes were super clear, as were her expectations. She's cute and funny, which made her easy to listen to in lectures, and she really knew her material. Her exams were apparently harder than the other profs', but I still think they were really fair for what we covered. A lot to memorize, but that goes with the course :P

An amazing prof and a wonderful person! Made orgo fun, teached with enthusiasm, and I actually looked forward to coming to class @ 8:30 in the morning. Assignments and exams highly reflected upon what was taught in class and held lot of office hours. The university needs more profs like her !!!

Can i put a 10 for clarity and helpfulness? Dr. Dion is FANTASTIC! She teaches you everything you need to know and she does it so well! You always know exactly what to expect and her exams are VERY similar to her homework. Absolutely wonderful prof and person! She made me want to take ORGO III.... let's hope she's the one teaching it
Amazing Prof, I love her. So clear and tests are very fair

SUCH A GREAT PROF, wants everyone to understand all the major concepts in organic chemistry, very good notes, attend her lectures, its not boring, very interesting, crystal clear, She's fine too !!!!!!
So awesome, i think im in love

Quite simply the greatest professor I have ever had. Her explanations, clear. Her teaching style, fantastic. She doesn't bs you. She teaches you what you need to know and she does it well. Her exams are fair- never expects anything she didn't mention. She is always there to hep and is extremely friend. Very happy I had her. UofO needs to keep her!

As a professor, she is very helpful and understands the material perfectly and is able to dish it out perfectly as well. However, the midterms were reasonable; the final really was harder... you need to attend class after the midterm, read the chapters on the materiel after the exam twice, and go to all the DGD's  . This is crucial to do great!
